Wash and dry all produce. Slice corn kernels off @corn on the cob{1}(sliced); discard cob. Dice @Roma tomato{1}(diced). Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}(minced). Zest and quarter @lime{1}(quartered). Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped) leaves and stems.

Heat a drizzle of oil and @butter{1%tbsp}(for corn) in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add corn and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and lightly charred, ~{4-6%minutes}. (TIP: If corn begins to pop, cover pan.) Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

== Lime Crema ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp} and lime zest. Add water, 1 tsp at a time, until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Chicken ==

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @Southwest seasoning{1%tbsp}. Sprinkle with @ancho chili powder{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4 servings; we sent more). Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp}(for chicken) in pan used for corn over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

To bowl with corn, stir in tomato, cilantro, and a few pinches of shallot (add as much or as little as you like). Taste and add lime juice, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. For a smoky kick, add a pinch of remaining @ancho chili powder{pinch}.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}. Divide warmed tortillas between plates and fill with chicken, corn salsa, and crema. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.